Kyle Hamilton, Ikem Ekwonu among biggest risers in post-Combine 2022 NFL Draft Big Board No touchdowns, field goals or points were scored, but the NFL Scouting Combine still produced winners and losers. Agents, coaches, scouts, executives and about 320 college prospects gathered last week in Indianapolis. The Post was on site to gather information in private conversations and collect 40-yard dash times, hand-size measurements, vertical-jump heights and more. Here is our updated top-25 Big Board for this year’s NFL Draft, including each player’s rank in parentheses from our first Big Board published on Jan. 13.